properties.areaDesc: Natrona County Lower Elevations; Green Mountains and Rattlesnake Range
properties.headline: High Wind Warning issued February 2 at 1:36AM MST until February 2 at 3:00AM MST by NWS Riverton WY
properties.description:
...High Wind Warning for parts of central Wyoming until 3 AM...

.Strong winds aloft and a tight pressure gradient will combine
for high winds across the Absaroka Mountains into the Cody
Foothills into tonight. High winds across southeast Fremont into
Natrona County are likely today as well.

* WHAT...Southwest winds 30 to 40 mph with gusts up to 60 mph.
Localized gusts to near 70 mph are possible on the south side
of Casper along Outer Drive.

* WHERE...Green Mountains and Rattlesnake Range and Natrona
County Lower Elevations, especially along Outer Drive.

* WHEN...Until 3 AM Sunday.

* IMPACTS...Mainly to transportation. A blow over risk for light
and high profile vehicles including camper trailers and semi
trucks.
properties.instruction:
Use caution if traveling. Please keep two hands on your steering
wheel in case of a sudden, strong wind gust. In a parking lot,
park into the wind to minimize the possibility of your car door
hitting another parked vehicle.

NWSheadline: HIGH WIND WARNING REMAINS IN EFFECT UNTIL 3 AM MST EARLY THIS MORNING
